        "id": "post_004",
        "title": "Why I Built 100 Websites in 30 Days (And Hosted Them on Netlify)",
        "date": "2026-04-12",
        "topic_id": "t_frontend",
        "tags": [
          "portfolio",
          "netlify"
        ],
        "content_summary": "A deep dive into the 100 Websites project. Discussing the CI/CD pipeline, overcoming builder fatigue, and why Netlify is my go-to for Jamstack.",
        "content_full": [
          "I built 100 websites in 30 days because I was done talking about what I could do. I wanted undeniable output and a faster production rhythm that clients could feel immediately.",
          "[IMAGE: Time-lapse style workstation scene with dozens of browser tabs and completed site previews, sticky note saying 'Day 18/30', realistic tech studio atmosphere.]",
          "The challenge forced me to standardize my stack. Netlify was the obvious choice because preview deploys, rollbacks, and clean CI/CD removed friction while I was shipping at high speed.",
          "The hard part was not code. It was consistency. Some days the creative energy was high, some days it was not. The system still had to work.",
          "By the end, I had a reusable component library and a clearer offer for local businesses: faster launch, less risk, and better quality control."
        ],
        "related_wiki_nodes": [
