      {
        "id": "post_005",
        "title": "Solving the 'Get Booked' Problem for VB Specialty Shops",
        "date": "2026-04-18",
        "topic_id": "t_local_growth",
        "tags": [
          "local-business",
          "booking-systems",
          "seo"
        ],
        "content_summary": "Many specialty businesses in Virginia Beach have great services but terrible booking flows. Here is how I use Netlify Serverless Functions to integrate seamless scheduling.",
        "content_full": [
          "I keep seeing the same problem in Virginia Beach: great service, weak booking flow. People land on the site, get interested, then bounce because booking feels confusing.",
          "[IMAGE: Split-screen comparison of a cluttered booking page vs a clean optimized booking page, with callouts showing friction points removed and conversion path simplified.]",
          "My fix starts with clarity. One main CTA, one short path to action, and no dead-end contact form pretending to be scheduling.",
          "On the technical side, I wire Netlify Functions to scheduling tools so requests are fast and consistent. If the scheduler API fails, fallback notifications still capture the lead.",
          "When this is done right, owners stop chasing missed calls and start getting confirmed appointments from their website."
        ],
        "related_wiki_nodes": [
          "wiki_vb_local_seo"
        ]
      },
