      {
        "id": "post_007",
        "title": "From Click to Confirmed Booking in Under 90 Seconds",
        "date": "2026-04-28",
        "topic_id": "t_local_growth",
        "tags": [
          "booking-systems",
          "local-business",
          "netlify"
        ],
        "content_summary": "Breaking down the exact booking funnel I ship for Virginia Beach specialty businesses: clear CTA hierarchy, short forms, serverless scheduling handoff, and confirmation UX that reduces drop-off.",
        "content_full": [
          "If a visitor cannot book in under 90 seconds, I assume the funnel is broken. This is the benchmark I use when I test every local business site before launch.",
          "[IMAGE: Person using a phone to complete a booking flow while a stopwatch overlay shows less than 90 seconds, clean interface with visible progress steps and confirmation screen.]",
          "The structure is simple: promise, proof, action. The page should explain who it is for, why to trust it, and what to do next without forcing people to scroll through fluff.",
          "I keep form fields minimal and place reassurance near action buttons: response time, service area, and what happens after submission.",
          "That mix of clear copy and resilient backend handoff is what turns traffic into confirmed revenue."
        ],
        "related_wiki_nodes": [
          "wiki_vb_booking_stack",
          "wiki_vb_local_seo"
        ]
      },
