        "content_summary": "A day-by-day look at my launch workflow for brand-new businesses. The goal: ship fast without skipping positioning, local SEO foundations, booking flow validation, or analytics setup.",
        "content_full": [
          "This seven-day sprint exists for one reason: new businesses cannot wait months to start getting traction. They need a focused launch system that produces leads quickly.",
          "[IMAGE: Calendar-style sprint timeline with each day color-coded and labeled with deliverables, overlaid on a laptop showing a live staging site ready for launch.]",
          "I start with positioning and offer clarity, then move into page assembly and conversion copy. SEO setup and analytics come before launch, not after.",
          "The sprint works because each day has one main outcome. No multitasking chaos, no random task switching, no endless revisions before anything goes live.",
          "By day seven, the business has a real website that can rank, convert, and be improved with actual data."
