      {
        "id": "post_012",
        "title": "Manifesto: From AI Shipper to Netlify Partner Architect",
        "date": "2026-04-19",
        "topic_id": "t_business",
        "tags": [
          "netlify",
          "llm-ops",
          "automation"
        ],
        "content_summary": "How I bridge AI experimentation and enterprise production using Netlify's composable platform, without defaulting to Next.js.",
        "content_full": [
          "I built this manifesto to define the delivery standard I want attached to my name: fast AI execution with production discipline. I am not chasing hype cycles. I am building systems that survive traffic, handoffs, audits, and growth.",
          "[IMAGE: Split scene showing a scrappy AI prototype workspace on the left and a polished enterprise deployment dashboard on the right, connected by a migration roadmap labeled 'Netlify Composable Path'.]",
          "The first half of my work is AI Shippers speed: prototype quickly, test assumptions, and ship proof in days. The second half is partner-grade hardening: stable build pipelines, rollout controls, observability, security boundaries, and performance targets.",
          "The Netlify architecture I deploy most for this bridge is practical: Agent Runners for reliable background AI execution, AI Gateway for model governance and spend controls, Blobs for structured app data patterns, and Global Edge for performance and consistency worldwide.",
          "I keep a strict no-Next.js policy in this practice because I optimize for composability and operational clarity. Astro, Vite, and React let teams move faster with less framework drag and cleaner long-term maintenance.",
